        "## 7.3 Model Interpretation Notes\n",
        "\n",
        "**How to read Logistic Regression coefficients:**\n",
        "- **Positive coefficient** → that feature increases churn probability (risk signal)\n",
        "- **Negative coefficient** → that feature decreases churn probability (retention signal)\n",
        "- Coefficients are on standardised features, so magnitudes are directly comparable\n",
        "\n",
        "**Key insight:** Unlike tree models, LR gives a clean linear story:  \n",
        "`P(churn) = sigmoid(w₁·x₁ + w₂·x₂ + ... + b)`  \n",
        "Each coefficient `wᵢ` tells you exactly how much a 1-std-deviation increase in that feature shifts churn log-odds.\n"
      ]
